# HanapKalinga — CI Gate

After completing any change — no matter how small — run the full local CI
check sequence before declaring the task done. Do not ask if you should run
the checks. Never tell the user the task is complete if any check is failing.

Run phases in order. Do not proceed to the next phase if the current one fails.

## CI sequence (matches `.github/workflows/ci.yml`)

### Phase 1 — Lint

```bash
npm install
npm run lint
```

Zero warnings allowed. Fix every lint error and warning before Phase 2.

### Phase 2 — Type check

```bash
cd packages/shared && npx tsc --noEmit
cd apps/web && npx tsc --noEmit
```

Fix every TypeScript error. Do not use `@ts-ignore` or `any` unless unavoidable.

### Phase 3 — Build

```bash
npm run build
```

Requires `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`,
`SUPABASE_URL`, and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` for the
web app build. If a new env var is needed, add it to `.env.example` with a
placeholder and document it.

### Phase 4 — Dependency audit

```bash
npm run audit:critical
```

### Phase 5 — Secrets scan

Search for accidentally committed secrets before committing:

```bash
! rg -n "\\bsk_[A-Za-z0-9]{16,}" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "*.js" .
! rg -n "SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE\\s*=" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "*.js" .
! rg -n "https://[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.r2\\.cloudflarestorage\\.com" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "*.js" .
! rg -n -P "(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)[A-Za-z\\d]{32,}" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "!**/node_modules/**" --glob "!**/.next/**" --glob "!apps/web/types/database.types.ts" .
! rg -n "NEXT_PUBLIC_[A-Z0-9_]+" apps/web/lib/supabase/service.ts apps/web/app/api
```

Never commit values for `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `CLOUDFLARE_R2_*` keys,
`RESEND_API_KEY`, or any token/password string.

## Other rules

- **Branches**: Never push to `main`. Use `fix/`, `feat/`, or `chore/` branches.
- **Env vars**: Never hardcode secrets. Add new vars to `.env.example`.
- **Migrations**: New schema changes only via new files in
  `packages/database/supabase/migrations/` — never edit existing migrations.
- **RLS**: Do not drop or modify existing RLS policies unless explicitly required.
- **Logging**: No `console.log` in production code. `console.error` in server catch
  blocks is allowed if it does not log sensitive data.

## Pre-push summary

After all phases pass, note CI results in the commit/PR description:

- Phase 1 (Lint): PASSED
- Phase 2 (Types): PASSED
- Phase 3 (Build): PASSED
- Phase 4 (Audit): PASSED
- Phase 5 (Secrets): PASSED
